        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:44PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 21
miles northwest of Big Timber, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Melville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
